Implemented NS-070 runtime emission wiring and landed it as commit `f66d2b6`.

- Wired runtime event emission across production paths:
  - `cmd_run` installs runtime emitter from `--log-format` in `src/main.rs`.
  - mint events in `src/orchestrator.rs`.
  - refresh events in `src/refresh.rs`.
  - revoke events in runtime revoke paths (`src/main.rs`, `src/integration_runtime.rs`).
  - child lifecycle events in `src/agent_process.rs`.
  - signal receive/forward events in `src/run_signal_wiring.rs`.
  - runtime emitter plumbing + stderr sink in `src/event.rs`.
- Added dedicated NS-070 wiring coverage in `src/event_emission_wiring_tests.rs`.
- Linus-style self-review found one semantic issue: SIGKILL escalation was initially logged before forward succeeded. I fixed ordering so `signal_forwarded` is emitted only after successful forwarding and added an edge-case test in `src/run_signal_wiring.rs`.
- Ran quality gates:
  - `cargo test`
  - `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`
- Posted provenance update:
  - requirement thread on `jn780pzjkgn2dq9geb9mqq7b4h83vcb9` (NS-070)
- Closed bead:
  - `noscope-7d5` closed as Completed
- Per your instruction, I did **not** push.
